<p>Thank you for submitting your application to King Edward VI College. After a thorough review of your application, it is evident that your academic aspirations align well with the ethos of our institution. I am pleased to extend a conditional offer, pending your successful attainment of the college's minimum entrance requirements.</p>

<p>To secure your place, we kindly request that you complete this form. Please ensure that you fill out the form by April 26, 2024. This offer is contingent upon your successful attainment of the college's minimum entrance requirements, which are as follows:</p>

<p>Programmes made up of three A Level subjects (or equivalent) require a minimum of six GCSE subjects at grade 5 or above.  Programmes made up of four A Level subjects (or equivalent) require a minimum of seven GCSE subjects at grade 7 or above.  Your subjects will also have minimum entrance requirements in addition to this. These can be found on each individual course page on our website: www.kedst.ac.uk/courses</p>

<p>Our entrance requirements are solely based on GCSE grades. BTECs and CNATs do not form part of our minimum entry requirements.</p>

<p>We have every confidence that you will continue to excel academically and maintain the level of commitment and dedication that has already shone through in your application.</p>

